    <title>Checksum Complement @ 0x800E</title>
    <description>16-bit big-endian checksum complement / additive byte sum target. Stock value is 0xB59A; MOD2 value is 0xB841. The firmware checksum routine compares the accumulated byte sum against this word.</description>
    <CATEGORYMEM index="0" category="4" />
    <EMBEDDEDDATA mmedaddress="0x800E" mmedelementsizebits="16" />
    <units>raw</units>
