    <description>Raw ROM view for the 3-byte descriptor triples consumed by routine 0x58F2. Observed callers point at 0x9131, 0x9134, 0x9137, 0x913A, 0x913D, 0x9143, 0x9146, 0x9149, 0x914C, 0x914F, 0x9152, 0x9155, 0x9158, 0x915B, 0x915E, 0x9161, 0x9164, and 0x9167. The 19x3 view includes the apparent reserved slot at 0x9140 to keep row alignment. This is service/state data, not a normal tune map.</description>
